<LI><B> Description </B>


<ul>										
<p align = "justify"> <span class = "content">
 This example program demonstrates reading of a file involving all the MPI process. The
program is independent of the number of processes that run it.
The new MPI library call  
<font face = "Courier New " size ="2"> 
MPI_File_get_size </font> library call is used to know about the size of the file which is stored
in bytes. MPI defines a type   
<font face = "Courier New " size ="2"> 
MPI_Offset  </font>, that is large enough to contain a file size. Each process writes the contents
of reading file. 

</span> </p>
